hoisting is javascript default of moving declaration to the top of the function ,if defined in a functiom, or  the global context,if outside a function .
var a; // variable declaration
var a=0;// variable initialization

 var a=10;
 
 var a;   
 a=10;
 
 // we write like the 
   ar a=10;
   document.write(a);
   var b=20;
  
  //compile phase
   var a;
   var b;
   a=10;
   document.write(a);
   b=20;
   
variable hoisting
 A variable can be used it has been declared.
 
 <!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head><title> variable hosting</title>
</head>
<body>
<script>	
         var a=80;
		 document.write(a);
		 
		 
 </script>
 
